<h3>
    <strong>1. North Santiam River (Stayton → Big Cliff Dam)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species &amp; Timing:</strong> Summer steelhead (May–Aug) frequently enter this clear-cool river, especially below Big Cliff Dam; occasional winter runs too. Statewide summer limit applies 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Public put-ins at Stayton, Packsaddle, Fisherman’s Bend, Mehama, and Green’s Bridge 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tactics:</strong> Drift or plunk roe, spinners, or swing flies. Hatchery-clipped steelhead may be kept, wild must be released – check fin status&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>2. South Santiam River (Foster Dam → Sweet Home)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species &amp; Timing:</strong> Similar to North Fork, summer steelhead show up May–Aug; winter run persists catch-and-release 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Bank fishing at Foster Dam area, Northside Park, Pleasant Valley Bridge, and Waterloo Park
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tactics:</strong> Fish deeper seams with bait rigs, bobber set-ups, and swing flies. Bait and hook rules vary, check regs
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>3. Mainstem Santiam (Stayton → Willamette Confluence)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species &amp; Timing:</strong> Continues steelhead runs, with decent summer action and wild winter fish
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Pullouts near Stayton, Jefferson, Fisherman’s Bend, and Green’s Bridge
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tips:</strong> Fish near junctions and current edges with spinners/plugs and bait drift rigs.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>4. Willamette River (Downstream to Salem)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species &amp; Timing:</strong> Summer steelhead run through Salem’s stretch (Island Park downstream), with winter runs common 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Easy bank and drift-fishing access at Salem parks and boat ramps 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tactics:</strong> Use float drift rigs, swing spinners/plugs, or centerpin setups in Edith Green areas.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>5. Siuslaw River (Estuary to Lake Creek) – Day Trip Route</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species &amp; Timing:</strong> Winter steelhead (Dec–Mar) make this drift-boat favorite 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Launch at Whittaker Creek, float downstream through rapids
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tactics:</strong> Roe plug bounce in faster currents; gravel pockets hold fish.
    </li>
</ul>
